{{Infobox company | name = Algerian Tractors Company ATC Spa |native_name = شركة الجرارات الجزائرية | logo = | logo_size = 204px | logo_alt = Massey Ferguson Logo | type = [[Public company|Public]],Subsidiary of [[AGCO]], [[Etrag]] | traded_as = | foundation = 16 August 2012<ref name="The Algerian Tractors Company">{{cite web|url=http://www.algerianembassy.org.uk/index.php/news/115-algerian-tractors-company.html|title=Algerian Tractors Company &#124; ATC &#8211; August 2012|publisher=algerianembassy.org.uk|accessdate=2016-03-17}}</ref> | founder = | location_city = [[Constantine Algeria|Constantine]] | location_country = Algeria | key_people = Mezdour Abdelhafid <small>(Chairman). | industry = [[Agriculture]] | products = [[Agricultural machinery]], consumer and commercial equipment, financial services, tractors. | revenue = | operating_income = DZD 1 146 &nbsp;million <small>(2013) | net_income = | assets = | equity = | num_employees = | homepage = http://www.etrag.dz/?p=105 }}
'''Algerian Tractors Company ATC Spa''', is a Join Venture company specialized in the development of agricultural machinery. It was created on August 16, 2012 after an agreement between the Algerian brand [[Etrag]] and the American Group [[AGCO]] based in [[El Khroub]], close to Constantine.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://investors.agcocorp.com/phoenix.zhtml?c=108419&p=irol-newsArticle&ID=1768286|title=AGCO {{!}} Investor Relations {{!}} News|website=investors.agcocorp.com|language=en|access-date=2017-09-07}}</ref>
==Partnership== Etrag concluded an industrial and commercial partnership with AGCO [[Massey Ferguson]],<ref name="businesswire">{{cite web|url=http://www.businesswire.com/news/home/20121218006342/en/AGCO-Starts-Local-Production-North-Africa|title=AGCO Starts Local Production in North Africa &#124; Business Wire|publisher=businesswire.com|accessdate=2016-03-17}}</ref> world leader in the manufacture of agricultural machinery. They created on 16 August 2012 a joint venture (joint venture) called Algerian Tractors Company ATC Spa. The agreement consisted of two local partners ETRAG with (36%), [[Pmat]] with (15%)and Massey Ferguson with (41%).<ref name="presse-dz">{{cite web|url=http://www.presse-dz.com/revue-de-presse/le-premier-tracteur-massey-ferguson|title=Le premier tracteur Massey Ferguson &#124; Presse-dz|publisher=presse-dz.com|accessdate=2016-03-17}}</ref>
==Products== The factory is producing several Massey Ferguson tractors and one Etrag tractor.
=== Massey Ferguson Models === *MF 440 Xtra 4x4 (82 CV) *MF 425 2x4 and 4x4 (55 CV) *MF 7150 4x4 (150 CV)
=== Etrag Models === *[[Cirta C6807]] 2x4 .
