{{Orphan|date=November 2013}}

The '''Asafotufiam Festival''' is celebrated by the chiefs and peoples of [[Ada, Ghana|Ada]] in the [[Dangbe East]] of the [[Greater Accra region]] of [[Ghana]].<ref name=Bak>{{cite web|title=Festivals in Ghana|url=http://www.ghanaweb.com/GhanaHomePage/tourism/festivals.php|publisher=www.ghanaweb.com|accessdate=27 December 2011}}</ref> The festival is celebrated in the first week  of August every year.<ref name=Bak/> It is celebrated in remembrance of the achievements in wars for settlements fought  by the ancestors of that area. A local dance called Kpatsa is performed to entertain the chief and the people.

