[[File:Bakkwa at a Bee Cheng Hiang store, Singapore - 20040111.jpg|thumb|''[[Bakkwa]]'' (roasted pork pieces) at a Bee Cheng Hiang store in Singapore]]
'''Bee Cheng Hiang''' ({{zh|c=美珍香|p=Měizhēnxiāng|poj=Bí-chin-hiang}}) is a company that produces [[Asian cuisine|Asian]]-style [[food]]stuffs, especially that of [[Cuisine of Singapore|Singaporean cuisine]]. Starting as a market stall in 1933 in [[Singapore]], the company has expanded its operations to more than 260 retail outlets located across nine territories—China, Hong Kong, Indonesia, Macau, Malaysia, the Philippines, South Korea, Singapore and Taiwan.<ref>{{cite book|author=Chwee Huat Tan|title=Financing for Entrepreneurs and Businesses|location=Singapore|publisher=[[National University of Singapore|NUS Press]]|year=2001|page=102|isbn=978-9971-69-248-3}}</ref>
Its known product is ''[[bakkwa]]''<ref>{{cite news |title=Going online for sweet meat |url=http://thestar.com.my/news/story.asp?file=/2007/2/16/asia/16900628&sec=asia |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110628191523/http://thestar.com.my/news/story.asp?file=%2F2007%2F2%2F16%2Fasia%2F16900628&sec=asia |dead-url=yes |archive-date=28 June 2011 |work=[[The Star (Malaysia)|The Star]] |location=Malaysia |date=16 February 2007 |accessdate=3 March 2011 |df= }}</ref>—smoked and roasted pieces of pork with a consistency similar to [[jerky (food)|jerky]]. Bee Cheng Hiang introduced "Gourmet Bakkwa" in 2003 (which is bacon-like slices of ''bakkwa''), and, in 2005, the "Chilli Gourmet Bakkwa". The company has evolved with the times and expanded its offerings to include prawn rolls, crispy [[pork floss]], [[cuttlefish]] and [[sausages]] etc.
