{{refimprove|date=May 2018}}

The '''Disaster Resource Network''' ('''DRN'''), an initiative of the [[World Economic Forum]], was the first non-governmental organization to donate to the [[United Nations]]' [[CERF]], a fund created to aid regions threatened by [[starvation]] and disasters, particularly [[Africa]]n [[nation]]s.  DRN organizes and mobilizes business sector resources to provide assistance in response to disasters around the world.

