{{Infobox film | name = Entre désir et incertitude | image = | alt = <!-- see WP:ALT --> | caption = | director = Abdelkader Lagtaâ | producer = Jean Lodato | screenplay = Abdelkader Lagtaâ | starring = | music = Pierre-Yves Lenik | cinematography = Cyril Collot | editing = Vincent Morgenstern | studio = | distributor = | released = {{Film date|2010}}<!-- {{Film date|Year|Month|Day|Location}} --> | runtime = 52 minutes | country = Morocco | language = | budget = | gross = }}
'''''Entre Désir et incertitude''''' is a [[Morocco|Moroccan]] 2010 documentary film.
== Synopsis == This is the first documentary film dedicated to [[Moroccan cinema]]; Between Desire and Uncertainty hands the microphone over to the filmmakers and film critics. Besides offering a brief historical approach, this documentary strives to identify the different movements that push Moroccan cinema. Likewise, it also makes very clear the dangers that threaten cinema's evolution.
