{{Infobox European Parliament constituency
|title = Essex North East
|map = Image:Europarl logo.svg
|mapcaption = [[European Parliament]] logo
|created = 1979
|dissolved = 1994
|meps = 1
|memberstate = United Kingdom
|sources = [http://www.election.demon.co.uk/]
}}
'''Essex North East''' was a [[European Parliament constituency|constituency]] of the [[European Parliament]] located in the [[United Kingdom]], electing one [[Member of the European Parliament]] by the [[first-past-the-post]] electoral system. Created in [[European Parliament election, 1979 (United Kingdom)|1979]] for the first elections to the European Parliament, it was abolished in 1994 and succeeded by the constituencies of [[Essex North and Suffolk South (European Parliament constituency)|Essex North and Suffolk South]] and [[Essex South (European Parliament constituency)|Essex South]].

==Boundaries==

On its creation in 1979, it consisted of the [[List of United Kingdom Parliament constituencies|parliamentary constituencies]] of [[Braintree (UK Parliament constituency)|Braintree]], [[Colchester (UK Parliament constituency)|Colchester]], [[South East Essex (UK Parliament constituency)|South East Essex]], [[Maldon (UK Parliament constituency)|Maldon]], [[Saffron Walden (UK Parliament constituency)|Saffron Walden]], [[Southend East (UK Parliament constituency)|Southend East]] and [[Southend West (UK Parliament constituency)|Southend West]].<ref>[[Boundary Commission for England]], ''European Assembly Constituencies'', December 1978.</ref>

After the 1984 boundary changes based on the new UK parliamentary constituencies created in 1983, it consisted of Braintree, [[Harwich (UK Parliament constituency)|Harwich]], North Colchester, [[Rochford (UK Parliament constituency)|Rochford]], Saffron Walden, [[South Colchester and Maldon (UK Parliament constituency)|South Colchester and Maldon]], Southend East and Southend West.<ref>European Parliament Information Office, ''MEPs and their constituencies'', December 1988</ref> Harwich had previously been part of the [[Suffolk (European Parliament constituency)|Suffolk]] constituency.

The constituency was abolished in 1994. Braintree, Harwich, North Colchester, Saffron Walden and South Colchester and Maldon became part of [[Essex North and Suffolk South (European Parliament constituency)|Essex North and Suffolk South]]. Rochford, Southend East and Southend West were now part of the new constituency of [[Essex South (European Parliament constituency)|Essex South]].<ref>''The European Parliament 1994-1999 : MEPs and European constituencies in the United Kingdom'', London : UK Office of the European Parliament, November 1994.</ref>

