[[File:Туполев Ту-22 , Полтава-4 RP2985.jpg|thumb|18 × FAB-500 general purpose bombs on two underwing pylons of a [[Tu-22M]]]]

The '''FAB-500''' is a [[Russian Air Force]] low-drag, general purpose, air-dropped bomb with a 500-kilogram high-explosive warhead. The first models of the bomb appeared in the early 1960s in the [[Soviet Union]].{{Citation needed|date=June 2018}} The bomb is unguided, features a single nose fuze, and is compatible with most models of Soviet aircraft.<ref name="FAB-500">{{cite web | title=FAB-500 | website=Guide to Military Equipment and Civil Aviation | date=2017-07-15 | url=http://www.deagel.com/Defensive-Weapons/FAB-500_a003491001.aspx | access-date=2018-03-15}}</ref> The FAB-500 has been used most recently over Syria by both Russian and Syrian warplanes.<ref name="War Is Boring 2017">{{cite web | title=The Su-22 Is Syria’s War-Weary Warhorse | website=War Is Boring | date=2017-02-15 | url=https://warisboring.com/the-su-22-is-syrias-war-weary-warhorse/ | access-date=2018-03-15}}</ref>

