{{Infobox monument
| dedicated_to  = [[Diogo Gomes]]
| image         = CV-praia-gomez.jpg
| caption       = Statue of Diogo Gomes
| location      = [[Praia]], [[Cape Verde]]
| designer      = [[Joaquim Correia]]
| complete      = 1956
| coordinates   = {{Coord|14.9159|-23.5096|display=it}}
| height        = {{convert|5.15|m|abbr=on}}
| material      = cast iron
}}
The '''Monumento de Diogo Gomes''' is a [[statue]] at the south end of the [[Plateau (Praia)|Plateau]], the historic centre of [[Praia]], on the island of [[Santiago, Cape Verde|Santiago]], [[Cape Verde]].<ref name=gomes>[http://hdl.handle.net/11328/594 Valor simbólico do centro histórico da Praia], Lourenço Conceição Gomes, Universidade Portucalense, 2008</ref>{{rp|157-159}} It represents [[Diogo Gomes]], the [[Portugal|Portuguese]] navigator who was one of the discoverers of the island of Santiago in 1460.<ref name=gomes/>{{rp|73}} The cast iron statue was created by the Portuguese sculptor [[Joaquim Correia]] in 1956. The statue itself is 3.3 m tall, and stands on a 1.85 m high pedestal.<ref name=gomes/>{{rp|157-159}} It stands close to the [[Presidential Palace of Cape Verde|Presidential Palace]], and overlooks the beach of [[Chã de Areia|Gamboa]].

