{{notability|date=February 2018}}
{{primary|date=February 2018}}
{{coi|date=February 2018}}
The '''Network Institute for Global Democratization''' (NIGD) is an organisation aimed at contributing to worldwide democratisation. The institute was established in 1997, with its headquarters in [[Helsinki]], [[Finland]] and a second office based in [[Lima]], [[Peru]].<ref>http://www.uia.org/s/or/en/1100021985 {{dead link|date=March 2015}}</ref>NIGD is a founding member of the international Council of the [[World Social Forum]]. 

==Goals and Activities==

NIGD is made up of a transnational network of 78 researchers and activists, who together strive to promote democratization.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://nigdwp.kaapeli.fi/?page_id=2|title=About|work=kaapeli.fi}}</ref>This network works to strengthen an incipient [[global civil society]] and define an alternative globalization through cross-cultural dialogue and concrete proposals for reform. 
To this end, its practices include original critical research and policy analysis, as well as organizing workshops, seminars and conferences and consultancy work. 

