{{Politics of the Republic of the Congo}}
Indirect '''presidential elections''' were held in the [[Republic of the Congo]] on 19 December 1963 after President [[Fulbert Youlou]] had been overthrown in a [[1963 Republic of the Congo coup d'état|coup]] on 15 August. [[Alphonse Massamba-Débat]] was the only candidate, and was elected unopposed.<ref>[[Dolf Sternberger]], [[Bernhard Vogel (politician)|Bernhard Vogel]], [[Dieter Nohlen]] & Klaus Landfried (1978) ''Die Wahl der Parlamente: Band II: Afrika, Erster Halbband'', p1053</ref>
